anyone else ever seen those big green worms called tomato worms when i had a farm in new mexico before i moved here to the imperial valley we used to find these giant green worms about as big as a cigar and people called them tomato worms maybe they were caterpillars coz you'd find them crawling on tree trunks pretty often i'm not making this up but they were smooth skinned not fuzzy and kids would gather round and go' eewwwwwwww till one kid would pick it off the tree and throw it against the tree or the ground and it would make this awful sound spa lohp kinda the sound an undercooked blood sausage makes when you cut into it and it explodes and all the kids would scream and scatter once the tomato worm was sufficiently mangled oh yeah a question i had a question anyone seen or heard of these tomato worms and if so are they poisonous to varmits like jackrabbits or moles coz if they are i'm a gonna git me some what do you think of that granny crabtree granny crabtree ma ah hero tyler yes sssssss hi greenthumb awesome i have a whole bunch of them buggers in my basement nicely tucked away in hellman's mayonnaise jars i feed them little prime cuts of garden moles or bbq mole skewers they love that stuff hahahaha Pat Garrett & Billy the Kid (album) Tomato Barbecue Hot dog Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Snake Hamburger Happy Tree Friends Rich Mullins Earthworm Codename: Kids Next Door Egg (food) Taboo food and drink The Grim Adventures of Billy and Mandy Aerial (dance move) The Marshall Mathers LP The SpongeBob SquarePants Movie Worms weapons and tools Olive RuneScape quests Dick and Dom in da Bungalow Cantonese cuisine Recurring South Park characters AFI 100 Years series Resident Evil Outbreak Mole (animal) Tobacco Empire Burlesque Blood on the Tracks D__ner kebab Mayonnaise Futurama (TV series - season 5) Sausage Professional wrestling throws SpongeBob SquarePants Pizza Joke Professional wrestling attacks Naruto jutsu Hip hop collaborations Teacher's Pet 